verses.verse: Praise <WH1984> ye the LORD <WH3050>. Praise <WH1984> the LORD <WH3068>, O my soul <WH5315>.
While I live <WH2416> will I praise <WH1984> the LORD <WH3068>: I will sing praises <WH2167> unto my God <WH430> while I have any being.
Put not your trust <WH982> in princes <WH5081>, nor in the son <WH1121> of man <WH120>, in whom there is no help <WH8668>.
His breath <WH7307> goeth forth <WH3318>, he returneth <WH7725> to his earth <WH127>; in that very day <WH3117> his thoughts <WH6250> perish <WH6>.
Happy <WH835> is he that hath the God <WH410> of Jacob <WH3290> for his help <WH5828>, whose hope <WH7664> is in the LORD <WH3068> his God <WH430>:
Which made <WH6213> heaven <WH8064>, and earth <WH776>, the sea <WH3220>, and all that therein is: which keepeth <WH8104> truth <WH571> for ever <WH5769>:
Which executeth <WH6213> judgment <WH4941> for the oppressed <WH6231>: which giveth <WH5414> food <WH3899> to the hungry <WH7457>. The LORD <WH3068> looseth <WH5425> the prisoners <WH631>:
The LORD <WH3068> openeth <WH6491> the eyes of the blind <WH5787>: the LORD <WH3068> raiseth <WH2210> them that are bowed down <WH3721>: the LORD <WH3068> loveth <WH157> the righteous <WH6662>:

The LORD <WH3068> preserveth <WH8104> the strangers <WH1616>; he relieveth <WH5749> the fatherless <WH3490> and widow <WH490>: but the way <WH1870> of the wicked <WH7563> he turneth upside down <WH5791>.
The LORD <WH3068> shall reign <WH4427> for ever <WH5769>, even thy God <WH430>, O Zion <WH6726>, unto all <WH1755> generations <WH1755>. Praise <WH1984> ye the LORD <WH3050>.
